'''Shipapu''' was a prominent location within the folklore and myth of the [[Azuposi]] people of the [[Pasocada Basin]] of northern [[Maztica]].
document_data.Mythology: Shipapu was a passage that connected the underworld with the "True World." The [[bird ]] [[Motsni]] used Shipapu to leave the underworld in search for a new land suitable for the Azuposi to live. The Azuposi also believed that when they died [[Masauwu]] would guide their [[spirit]] to the underworld through Shipapu.
